Topic A 

osi : open system interconnection mdoel 
network : node+link
LAN : directly linked nodes
WAN : connected LAN 
OSI : 7 layer 
protocol : structed format 
addressing: locate 
encapsulation : payload abstraction 
encapsulation : header + payload 
peer layer : protocol running at same layer 
same layer interaction : communication bewteen nodes 
adjacant layer interaction: service user and provider 
protocol data unit (pdu) : encapsulation process 
------------------------------------------------
layer 1 : transmision on physical segment 
node : any device with network interface 
station : any node on wireless network 
host : end device 
link : physical media 
(physical) segment : all nodes which same the same link 
device : transceiver, repeater, hubs, media converter, modems 
transceiver: ? 
repeater : amplifier on media 
hubs : multiport repeater 
media converter : convert signal type 
modems : special converter for digial-analog
------------------------------------------------
layer 2 : transmision on logical segement 
data link layer : layer 2 
local address : hardware address 
hardware address : address used to identify host on local network 
local network : linked by 1 or more central nodes 
logical segement : node can sent data to another node (via central node)
local network == logical segement 
logical topology : layer 2 segement include mutile layer 1 segements
frame: unit in layer 2 
frame = dest + srcs + plod + erck 
payload : network packet 
header : dest + srcs 
error check : trucate check / corruption 
* media access method : how nodes can share media 
contention : ? 
ring based topology : 
device : adapters, NIC, bridges, switch, APs
network interface : NIC 
adapter : NIC 
NIC : assembling / disasembling frames for host and network media
bridge : stacks of NIC on each port to link central nodes 
switch : advanced bridge with better traffic control 
APs : wireless access point 
wireless access point : bridge for wired and wireless nodes  
MAC : media access control 
* media access control : physical segment control (1) 
LLC : logical acess control 
logical access control : standard network-layer (3) service interface 
pdu : frame 

-----------------------------------------------

layer 3 : moving data around a network of network (internet)
logical network : 
host id : 
router :
pdu : packet 
packet : unit in layer 3 
device : router, layer 3 switch 
wan router : router connect to internet 
router : wan router - subnet 
subnet : segement (1)
backbone : link between subnet's central node and router 


--------------------------------------------
layer 4 : moving frame and datagram between nodes and networks 
transport layer : end 2 end, host to host layer 
port number : identify application 
segments : unit in layer 4 
pdu : segments 
multiplexed : host transmitting mutiple packet(?) at same time 
